  and evaluates 230 cadets located at the Virginia Military Institute and the Virginia Women s Institute for Leadership  Maj Beaver enlisted in the Air Force in 1989 as a Communications Computer Systems Operator  She completed her bachelor s degree in Computer Science via the Airman Education and Commissioning Program and subsequently obtained her commission upon completion of Officer Training School in 2000  After she completed her initial Cyberspace Operations Officer training  she transferred to Germany where she served in various Communications Group and Squadron positions at Sembach and Ramstein Air Bases  She left Germany to pursue her master s degree in Computer Science at the Air Force Institute of Technology at Wright Patterson Air Force Base  Ohio  Upon graduating from the master s program  Maj Beaver transferred to Hurlburt Field  Florida where she worked on the Air Force Special Operations Command headquarters staff  The majority of her time on the special operations staff was spent in the Communications Plans and Programs branch and the Programming office  but she also performed Executive Officer duties for Lt Gen Bradley Heithold  Maj Beaver left Hurlburt Field to continue her service in support of the Air Force Intelligence  Surveillance  and Reconnaissance Agency at Lackland Air Force Base in San Antonio  Texas  While there  she served as the Chief of the Enterprise Management Branch within the Communications Directorate and the Deputy Chief of the Maintenance Division within the Directorate for Logistics  Installations  and Mission Support  Maj Beaver deployed in 2006 in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  She spent the bulk of her deployed time at Joint Base Balad where she conducted interviews and collected information on recent and ongoing operations for United States Special Operations Command  Maj Beaver was selected for promotion to Lieutenant Colonel and expects to have the new rank on by the end of 2015  EDUCATION 2000 Bachelor of Science Degree  Computer Science  University of South Carolina  Columbia  SC 2001 Air and Space Basics Course  Maxwell AFB  AL 2005 Master of Science Degree  Computer Science  Air Force Institute of Technology  Wright Patterson AFB  OH 2006 Squadron Officer School  Maxwell AFB  AL 2013 Air Command and Staff College  Correspondence  ASSIGNMENTS 1  Dec 2000   Jun 2001  Support Flight Commander  886th Communications Squadron  Sembach Air Base  Germany 2  Jun 2001   May 2002  Officer in Charge  Information Systems Support Section  786th Communications Squadron  Ramstein Air Base  Germany 3  May 2002   Aug 2003  Officer in Charge  Plans and Mobility  86th Communications Group  Ramstein Air Base  Germany 4  Aug 2003   Jun 2005  Student  Air Force Institute of Technology Masters Program  Wright Patterson AFB  OH 5  Jun 2005   Nov 2006  Officer in Charge  Requirements and Chief Information Officer Support  Communications Directorate  Air Force Special Operations Command  Hurlburt Field  FL 6  Nov 2006   Oct 2007  Chief  Command  Control  Communications  Computers  and Intelligence Programs  Plans  Programs  Requirements  and Assessments Directorate  Air Force Special Operations Command  Hurlburt Field  FL 7  Oct 2007   Oct 2008  Executive Officer to the Director  Plans  Programs  Requirements  and Assessments  Air Force Special Operations Command  Hurlburt Field  FL 8  Oct 2008   Jun 2009  Chief  Command  Control  Communications  Computers  and Intelligence Programs  Plans  Programs  Requirements  and Assessments Directorate  Air Force Special Operations Command  Hurlburt Field  FL 9  Jun 2009   Sep 2011  Chief  Enterprise Management Branch  Communications Directorate  Air Force Intelligence  Surveillance  and Reconnaissance Agency  Lackland AFB  TX 10  Sep 2011   July 2013  Deputy Chief  Maintenance Division  Logistics  Installations  and Mission Support Directorate  Air Force Intelligence  Surveillance  and Reconnaissance Agency  Lackland AFB  TX 11  July 2013   Present  Operations Officer  Air Force Reserve Officer Training Corps  Detachment 880  Virginia Military Institute  Lexington  VA MAJOR AWARDS AND DECORATIONS Meritorious Service Medal Air Force Commendation Medal with one oak leaf cluster Army Commendation Medal Air Force Achievement Medal with one oak leaf cluster Combat Readiness Medal Air Force Good Conduct Medal with two oak leaf clusters Iraq Campaign Medal OTHER ACHIEVEMENTS Distinguished Graduate  Basic Communications Officer Training Top Third Graduate  Squadron Officer School Federal Women s History Month Professional Field Grade Officer of the Year  JB San Antonio Numerous Unit level CGO and FGO Quarterly and Annual Awards EFFECTIVE DATES OF PROMOTION Second Lieutenant August 18  2000 First Lieutenant August 18  2002 Captain August 18  2004 Major July 1  2010 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 